The paper proposes a framework for modeling event sequences using temporal point processes (TPPs) and normalizing flows. This involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and probabilistic modeling, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
